The paper discusses the concept of differential privacy, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). It also involves statistical analysis and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) for implementing private mechanisms. Finally, the paper touches on the applications of differential privacy in various domains, such as social sciences and healthcare (cs.SI).
